---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ChapterStyles from '../components/ChapterStyles.astro';

const lessons = [
  { icon: '$', label: 'reliability as the benchmark', body: "Backtest-beautiful strategies that lost on day three got killed ruthlessly. That's where my reliability thesis sharpened — it isn't a feature, it's the whole game." },
  { icon: '◑', label: 'four algos, one discipline', body: 'Four proprietary strategies around risk and money management. Risk/money management isn\'t the boring part — it\'s the part that decides whether any of the cool algorithms actually get to run tomorrow.' },
  { icon: '▤', label: 'building the whole stack', body: 'Login, algorithm deployment, precise execution, analytics — I built all of it from blank slate. No PM, no SRE, no "data team" to ask. First real taste of what a founder actually owns.' },
  { icon: '⚙', label: 'ai + markets', body: 'Stock-analysis app: Yahoo Finance pipelines, technical indicators, volume analysis, news sentiment via Google News, statistical insights, ARIMA forecasts. The seed of everything PortoAI became.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="The 2023 Pivot — Venkateshwar Reddy Jambula">
  <ChapterStyles />
  <article class="ch">
    <header class="ch-header">
      <a href="/" class="ch-back">&larr; home</a>
      <div class="ch-eyebrow">June 2023 – May 2024 &middot; solo &middot; Founder &amp; Quantitative Researcher</div>
      <h1>The quiet year.</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="ch-opener">
      <p class="ch-lede">
        I left Samsung in mid-2023 to build an automated trading system
        from zero &mdash; alone, unfunded, no deck, no stealth branding.
        Just me, a laptop, and Indian options markets that
        <em>didn&rsquo;t care</em> about my previous titles.
      </p>
      <figure class="feature-photo">
        <img src="/images/stealth/terminal.jpg" alt="Trading terminal with financial data" loading="eager" />
        <figcaption>the tools &middot; the quietest year of my career</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section">
      <h2>Why I left a Chief-level role.</h2>
      <p>
        On paper it looked crazy. At Samsung I had the title, the salary,
        the team, the comfortable Bangalore life. I walked away to be solo
        for a year.
      </p>
      <p>
        The reason was simple: I could see the LLM wave coming and I wanted
        to understand it without an org chart in the way. So I built an
        end-to-end automated trading system that used AI as the decision
        layer &mdash; and spent a year learning exactly where that layer
        breaks down under real, non-stationary markets.
      </p>
      <p>
        The trading <em>was</em> the research. Every failure mode that
        showed up &mdash; fixation, decision drift, reward hacking,
        overfitting to recent conditions &mdash; is the exact same failure
        mode I now name in <a href="https://github.com/Venkateshwar-Reddy-Jambula/coherencebench">CoherenceBench</a>.
        The benchmark came from the broken P&amp;L statement, not the
        other way around.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section">
      <h2>What I built.</h2>
      <div class="lesson-grid">
        {lessons.map((l) => (
          <article class="lesson">
            <div class="l-icon">{l.icon}</div>
            <div class="l-label">{l.label}</div>
            <p>{l.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section">
      <h2>The surface area.</h2>
      <div class="gallery g-3">
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/stealth/candles.jpg" alt="Candlestick chart" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>candles &middot; the language of the day</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/stealth/terminal.jpg" alt="Trading terminal" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>terminal &middot; where every decision lived</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/stealth/bse.jpg" alt="Bombay Stock Exchange" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>BSE &middot; the market I studied, mostly humbled by</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p class="photo-credit">Photos: Wikimedia Commons (CC).</p>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section ch-close">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          A year later I wasn&rsquo;t rich, but I was <em>educated</em> in
          a way nothing else in my career had matched. The instincts I
          formed in those twelve months &mdash; about reliability, about
          long-horizon coherence, about how much of an AI system&rsquo;s
          value lives in what it <em>refuses</em> to do &mdash; are what
          PranaAlpha Labs is built on today.
        </p>
        <p>
          That year&rsquo;s instincts are what keep PortoAI honest. If an
          agent can&rsquo;t stay coherent across a trading day, it has no
          business touching anyone else&rsquo;s portfolio.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <footer class="ch-foot"><a href="/" class="ch-back-cta">&larr; back to the story</a></footer>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
